he thing that is defeating it. The capacity for reformation and change lies within.', 5352, 0), (397931, 'The most amazing thing about little children ... was their fantastic adaptability.', 62852, 0), (397932, 'Let a man turn to his own childhood-no further-if he will renew his sense of remoteness  and of the mystery of change.', 62853, 0), (397933, 'All love shifts and changes. I don''t know if you can be wholeheartedly in love all the time.', 62854, 0), (397934, 'People change and forget to tell each other.', 1991, 0), (397935, 'When you have a baby  you set off an explosion in your marriage  and when the dust settles  your marriage is different from what it was. Not better  necessarily  not worse  necessarily  but different.', 301, 0), (397936, 'There is change in all things. You yourself are subject to continual change and some decay  and this is common to the entire universe.', 267, 0), (397937, 'No one can persuade another to change. Each of us guards a gate of change that can only be opened from the inside. We cannot open the gate of another  either by argument or emotional appeal.', 62855, 0), (397938, 'We measure success and depth by length and time  but it is possible to have a deep relationship that doesn''t always stay the same.', 62514, 0), (397939, 'One of the dreariest spots on life''s road is the point of conviction that nothing will ever again happen to you.', 14686, 0), (397940, 'I realized that if what we call human nature can be changed  then absolutely anything is possible. And from that moment  my life changed.', 25662, 0), (397941, 'A woman''s life can really be a succession of lives  each revolving around some emotionally compelling situation or challenge  and each marked off by some intense experience.', 62856, 0), (397942, 'Readjusting is a painful process  but most of us need it at one time or another.', 62857, 0), (397943, 'For many men  the acquisition of wealth does not end their troubles  it only changes them.', 62237, 0), (397944, 'O